- Controller: App\Http\Controllers\Api\V1\PostCommentController@store handles POST /v1/posts/{post}/comments and returns a CommentResource constructed from the authenticated user's created comment; it also broadcasts a CommentPosted event.
- Request validation: App\Http\Requests\Api\CommentsRequest requires 'content' (required). Therefore the requestBody is application/json with a required string property "content".
- Path parameter: the route parameter {post} is route-model-bound to App\Models\Post; the controller type-hints Post $post, so the path parameter represents a Post identifier (modeled here as an integer id).
- Response: store returns a CommentResource (JsonResource) representing the comment as an object with fields provided by App\Http\Resources\Comment: id, content, posted_at (ISO8601), humanized_posted_at, author_id, post_id, author_name, author_url, can_delete. The controller does not explicitly set a different HTTP status, so the response is modeled as 200 OK with application/json containing that object.
- Validation errors: since the request uses FormRequest validation, include 422 Unprocessable Entity response with the typical Laravel validation error structure.

